# No emojis

**Do not use pictographic / multi-codepoint emojis** in code or markdown files (e.g. pictographic symbols used as decoration, skin-tone or ZWJ sequences).

**Unicode characters are acceptable**, including codepoints that happen to fall in the emoji range when used as symbols (e.g. checkmarks, arrows, bullets).

Repositories may document stricter checks (scripts, pre-commit); follow those when present.
